    {
      "id": "c64586e4c286f871a759002c304e87d427233195",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-06-12 09:56:39.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> I will keep and eye out for this. Even if this patch gets picked up\n > by Oleg, I will open a new bug to fix the checkpatch warnings.\n > \n > Or...\n > \n > Shall I submit the refreshed patch with checkpatch fixes either way\n > ?\n\nI wouldn't give the patch a +1 or +2 if I didn't think it could be landed as-is.  My recommendation is to leave it as-is and land the fixes that it is making now (which also avoids the overhead of having to reinspect and retest the patch), but if it cannot land for some reason (conflict with some other patch landed earlier) then it would be fine to fix the other minor checkpatch issues.\n\nIMHO, it is better to land a patch that makes an improvement, and then make a second patch that adds more improvements, rather than never finish landing a patch that makes 100 improvements (which may also be too complex to inspect properly).\n\nAre you going to submit patches to fix up the indentation for other files?  It wouldn't be terrible to have patches that clean up the indentation of remaining files so we can finally get the space-to-tab conversion behind us.  Please submit one patch per file, submitted separately instead of in a series, all marked \"Test-Parameters: trivial\" so that they can be tested, inspected, and landed independently.  Just a handful at a time is probably best, so you don't spend too much time rebasing before the patches are inspected and landed (if there is too much contention on a file it may need to be split into sub-file chunks).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "d3899bf32e04cae64e8488bf7d4e51df24026b59",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 655,
        "name": "Arshad Hussain",
        "email": "arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com",
        "username": "arshad512"
      },
      "date": "2018-06-12 13:01:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n>I wouldn't give the patch a +1 or +2 ... <snip> \nUnderstood.\n\n>IMHO, it is better to land a patch that makes an improvement, and then make a second patch that adds more improvements, rather than never finish landing a patch that makes 100 improvements (which may also be too complex to inspect properly).\nI Agree.\n\nAre you going to submit patches to fix up the indentation for other files? \nYes!, certainly I will. \n\nThanks\nArshad",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
